      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of picture caption with June 28 article on sentencing of former New York City police officers for roles in assault on Abner Louima, which reversed names of Thomas Wiese and Thomas Bruder</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A picture caption yesterday about the sentencing of three former New York City police officers for their roles in the assault on Abner Louima reversed the names of two of the ex-officers. Thomas Wiese was in the foreground of the left picture, and Thomas Bruder was at right in the center picture.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A picture caption yesterday about the sentencing of three former New York City police officers for their roles in the assault on Abner Louima reversed the names of two of the ex-officers. Thomas Wiese was in the foreground of the left picture, and Thomas Bruder was at right in the center picture.</p>
      </block>
